data.title: What’s Coming to Netflix in September 2024
data.meta_description: "Emily in Paris" Season 4 Part 2, "Selling Sunset" Season 8, "Uglies" and more are coming to Netflix in September.
data.text:
Vive la France! Part 2 of “Emily in Paris” Season 4 comes to Netflix on Sept. 12. The second half of the fourth season sees the aspiring fashion mogul skiing in the French Alps and leaving her adopted home of Paris for a Roman holiday. The Netflix original film “Uglies” starring Joey King also hits the streamer in September, following a young woman’s journey through a futuristic dystopia with mandated beauty standards.

On Sept. 6, Season 8 of “Selling Sunset” premieres on Netflix. In the new season, the Oppenheim Group welcomes a new agent to their ranks while having to let go of a close friend.

Plus, Season 2 of “Outlast,” Season 7 of “The Circle” and the new Netflix original film “Rebel Ridge” hit the streamer in September.

Take a look below for Netflix’s full September schedule.
